+# Why CVE-2026-49271 Does Not Affect `libheif` 1.11.0 on Debian Bullseye
+
+## CVE-2026-49271 – Out-of-Bounds Read via Wrapped `icef` Offset Check in Uncompressed Decoder
+
+- **Component:** `unc_decoder::get_compressed_image_data_uncompressed` (`libheif/codecs/uncompressed/unc_decoder.cc`)
+- **CWE:** CWE-125 (Out-of-bounds Read)
+- **Issue:** Explicit `icef` compressed-unit offsets are validated with `unit_offset + unit_size`. Because the addition can wrap, a crafted HEIF file can pass the range check and construct a vector from iterators outside the compressed item buffer, producing an out-of-bounds heap read and crash.
+- **Upstream Status:** Fixed in upstream `libheif` 1.22.1
+
+---
+
+## Why Debian Bullseye (`libheif` 1.11.0-1+deb11u2) Is NOT Affected
+
+The vulnerability is confined to the **uncompressed HEIF decoder** (`cmpC` / `icef` handling under `libheif/codecs/uncompressed/`). That codec was introduced experimentally in upstream **libheif 1.16.0**, after Bullseye's 1.11.0 baseline.
+
+In v1.11.0:
+
+- There is no uncompressed codec, `unc_decoder`, `icef` parser, or `cmpC` property handling
+- The wrapped range-check code path cannot be reached
+
+### Verification
+
+```bash
+grep -rn "get_compressed_image_data_uncompressed\|icef\|unit_offset" libheif/  # empty
+ls libheif/codecs/uncompressed/unc_decoder.cc                                 # missing
+```
+
