+# Why CVE-2026-47178 Does Not Affect `libheif` 1.11.0 on Debian Bullseye
+
+## CVE-2026-47178 – Heap Out-of-Bounds Write in Uncompressed (`unci`) Tile Decoder
+
+- **Component:** `unc_decoder_component_interleave::decode_tile()` (`libheif/codecs/uncompressed/`)
+- **CWE:** CWE-787 (Out-of-bounds Write)
+- **Issue:** For tiled, component-interleaved, 4:2:0 uncompressed HEIF images, the destination row offset uses full-resolution tile origin `out_y0` against an already chroma-halved `dst_plane_stride`, producing a heap OOB write.
+- **Fix Commit:** `62d60530610110fc7bc6d08ff30f2cf23917a1eb`
+- **Upstream Status:** Fixed in upstream `libheif` 1.22.0; advisory affected range is **>= 1.19.0**
