+## Why Debian Bullseye (`libheif` 1.11.0-1+deb11u2) Is NOT Affected
+
+The uncompressed (`unci`) codec subsystem was introduced experimentally in upstream **libheif 1.16.0**. The vulnerable component-interleave tile decoder path and the advisory's affected range begin at **1.19.0**.
+
+In v1.11.0:
+
+- There is no `libheif/codecs/uncompressed/` directory
+- There is no `unc_decoder_component_interleave`, `cmpC`, or `unci` decode path
+- `WITH_UNCOMPRESSED_CODEC` does not exist
+
+Debian security tracker version comparison may flag 1.11.0 as vulnerable based on a broad upper bound; that match is a false positive because the vulnerable code is not present.
+
