+# Why CVE-2026-41069 Does Not Affect `libheif` 1.11.0 on Debian Bullseye
+
+## CVE-2026-41069 – Out-of-bounds Read via Empty Chunks in `SampleAuxInfoReader`
+
+- **Component:** `SampleAuxInfoReader` constructor / `Track::load()` (HEIF sequences-track parsing)
+- **CWE:** CWE-125 (Out-of-bounds Read)
+- **Issue:** When `stco.entry_count == 0` and `saio.entry_count == 0` but `saiz.sample_count > 0`, validation passes trivially (`0 == 0`) and the constructor evaluates `chunks[0]` on an empty vector.
+- **Fix Commit:** `71755d3d41a117685a3274bdd1214fc50a760f20`
+- **Upstream Status:** Fixed in upstream `libheif` 1.22.0
+
+---
+
+## Why Debian Bullseye (`libheif` 1.11.0-1+deb11u2) Is NOT Affected
+
+This is a companion to **CVE-2026-41071**. Both live in the sequences-track `SampleAuxInfoReader` subsystem introduced in upstream **libheif 1.20.0**.
+
+In v1.11.0 none of the required constructs exist:
+
+- No `libheif/sequences/` directory or `track.cc`
+- No `SampleAuxInfoReader`, `Box_saiz`, `Box_saio`, or `Box_stco`
+- No track / sequence decode path
+
+### Verification
+
+```bash
+grep -rn "SampleAuxInfoReader\|Box_saiz\|Box_saio\|Box_stco" libheif/   # empty
+find . -iname '*sequence*' -o -iname '*track*'                            # no matches in sources
+```
+
+### Debian Bullseye Package Details
+
+| Field | Value |
+|-------|-------|
+| Package | libheif |
+| Version | 1.11.0-1+deb11u2 |
+| Distribution | Debian 11 (Bullseye) |
+| Upstream Version | 1.11.0 |
+| Status | **NOT AFFECTED** |
+
+**Status: NOT_AFFECTED — No action needed.**
